1. The fat oxidation rate was measured in the CHO.
2. The fat oxidation rate was measured in the CON.
3. The fat oxidation rate in the CHO was significantly lower than in the CON.
4. The fat oxidation rate was measured while walking.
5. The fat oxidation rate was measured for different time intervals.
6. The time intervals were 5~15 minutes, 25~35 minutes, and 45~55 minutes.
7. The fat oxidation rate in the CHO was significantly lower than the CON during the 5~15 minute interval.
8. The fat oxidation rate in the CHO was significantly lower than the CON during the 25~35 minute interval.
9. The fat oxidation rate in the CHO was significantly lower than the CON during the 45~55 minute interval.
